Text Delimiters

When adding delimiters between inline text elements, use the **middle dot** character (`·`, U+00B7) instead of the **bullet** character (`•`, U+2022).

```tsx
// ✅ Correct — use middle dot
<span>Item A · Item B · Item C</span>

// ❌ Incorrect — don't use bullet
<span>Item A • Item B • Item C</span>
```

The middle dot (`·`) is the preferred separator for inline metadata, breadcrumbs, and other text where items are delimited horizontally.
